Michael's is my favorite place to have things framed.
The selection of frames is huge.
They have a good selection of acid free papers and lots of choices for cuts and bevels as well.
Their prices are reasonable, even more reasonable if you wait for their half off framing coupons that appear in the newspaper at least twice a month.
I have had no less than 50 lithos, photos, paintings and such framed by Michael's and they have never damaged anything or caused me worry over any of them.
They are not the quickest, but they have work done when they say it will be done.

I'll be honest.
In a craft superstore brawl, I'm putting my money on Joann's.
Michael's never seems to cut it.
This Michael's is middle of the road.
Slightly dumpy appearance but clean over all.
Decent sales and random craft crap to appease the old folks.
The staff is sometimes friendly.
I'm a knitter and they have an okay selection of yarn.
Their book selection sucks and they really only have 1/2 of an aisle dedicated to knitting and crocheting stuff.
But, I did walk out of there with 7 balls of yarn for $14 and that's a steal compared to the damage I've done on other trips to other stores.

